This paper deals with performance analysis of quality link metrics in wireless multi-hop networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of distance vector routing protocol (DSDV), which is a common topic in the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). The comparison of different metrics and their impact on performance parameters involves statistical analysis, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses the security aspect of the metrics, which can be related to the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR).
